<h2 id="guidelines">Guidelines</h2>
<h3 id="hard-code">Don't hard code values</h3>
<p>Facebook <a href="https://www.slideshare.net/maxdesign/css-oocss-and-smacss/16-FacebookFacebook_blue_261_Unique_colors" target="_blank" rel="noopener">famously</a> had 548 unique colors hard-coded 6,498 times across their stylesheets. A total maintenance meltdown! Custom properties help you avoid this by enabling you to set up a shared single source of truth for the unique values in the design system. Reference them instead of copying and hard coding their values:</p>
<code-sample mode="css" readonly="readonly">
/* Do */
@import "../node_modules/m-/dist/custom-props.css";
#foo \{
  background-color: var(--color-gray-2);
}

/* Don't */
#foo \{
  background-color: #cccccc;
}
</code-sample>
